value.value: This MecI is a methicillin-resistant repressor resembling MecC. It confers resistance to penams.
eptB is a phosphoethanolamine transferase. It confers resistance to peptide antibiotics.
CrcB is part of the Camphor Resistance Protein Family. It confers resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics.
LpsB is involved in lipopolysaccharide synthesis. It provides intrinsic resistance to colistin and other peptide antibiotics such as polymyxins.
LpsB is involved in lipopolysaccharide synthesis. It confers intrinsic resistance to colistin and other peptide antibiotics.
LpsA plays a role in Lipooligosaccharide biosynthesis. LpsA confers resistance to polymyxin antibiotics.
ArnT is involved in Cell Wall Biosynthesis, specifically 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose (Ara4N). It confers resistance to peptide antibiotics.
Tet(X6) is a tetracycline inactivating enzyme. It is a tet(X) variant.
Tet(X5) is a tetracycline inactivating enzyme. It is a variant of tet(X).

ABC transporter complex which is involved in a phospholipid transport pathway that maintains lipid asymmetry in the outer membrane by retrograde trafficking of phospholipids from the outer membrane to the inner membrane.
LptD is involved in LPS transport in a ABC Transporter efflux system. It confers resistance to rifamycin, aminocoumarin, and peptide antibiotics.
A class D OXA-like beta-lactamase described in the emerging pathogen Cupriavidus gilardii.
A novel aminoglycoside resistance gene identified from Cupriavidus gilardii; AAC(3)-IVb / aacC10 is an aminoglycoside-3-N-acetyltransferase gene which confers resistance to gentamicin and tobramycin.
A novel aminoglycoside 3''-adenyltransferase gene and aminoglycoside resistance gene identified from Cupriavidus gilardii. ANT(3'')-Ib / aadA32 confers resistance to spectinomycin and streptomycin.
cprR is one part of a two-component regulatory system. It with its counterpart cprS induce the Arn operon to confer resistance to peptide antibiotics.
cprS is part of a two-component regulatory system that, with its counterpart cprR, induces the Arn operon in the presence of cationic peptides to confer resistance.
cprRS is a two-component regulatory system. In the presence of cationic peptides, it induces the Arn operon to confer resistance.

parRS is a two-component sensor that mediates MexXY/OprM and porin OprD to confer resistance to polycationic antibiotics. It has multiple mechanisms of resistance such as LPS modification, efflux mediation and reduced porin pathway.
ParS is the sensor component of the two-component ParRS system. Alongside its counterpart ParR, it confers resistance to polycationic antibiotics though regulation of efflux pumps and porins.
ParR is a component of the two-component sensor ParRS. Alongside its counterpart ParS, it confers resistance to polycationic antibiotics through the regulation of efflux components and porins.

rsmA is a gene that regulates virulence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. However, its negative effect on MexEF-OprN overexpression has been noted to confer resistance to various antibiotics. It's Escherichia coli homolog is csrA.
A glycopeptide antibiotic which binds to essential peptidoglycan hydrolases, thereby preventing autolysis and inhibited cell wall remodelling during growth.
A glycopeptide antibiotic which binds to essential peptidoglycan hydrolases, thereby preventing autolysis and cell wall remodelling.

definition.value: ROB-13 is a beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was found in Bibersteinia trehalosi.
ROB-3 is a beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was found in Moraxella pluranimalium.
ROB-4 is a beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was found in Moraxella porci.
ROB-5 is a class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was found in Moraxella sp. RCAD0137.

value.value: ROB-6 is a class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was first described by Clemente et al.
ROB-7 is a class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was first described by Clemente et al.
ROB-8 is a class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was first described by Clemente et al.
ROB-2 is an extended spectrum class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family It is described by Kadlec et al.

definition.value: ROB-10 is a class A beta-lactamase from the blaROB AMR gene family. It was found in Glaesserella parasuis.

label.value: Thermus thermophilus uL3 mutations conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics

value.value: Thermus thermophilus ribosomal protein uL3 containing various mutations conferring resistance to tiamulin. Mutations in the ribosomal protein of uL3 acts by interfering with local rRNA conformation thus conferring resistance.

label.value: Ribosomal protein mutation conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics

value.value: Ribosomal protein mutations that interfere with the rRNA conformation at the active site thus conferring antibiotic resistance.

label.value: Thermus thermophilus 23s rRNA conferring resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics

value.value: Mutations in the 23s rRNA of Thermus thermophilus confers resistance to pleuromutilin antibiotics such as tiamulin.
dfrA31 is an antibiotic resistance dihydrofolate reductase from an integron found from Vibrio cholerae.
AAC(3)-IIg is part of the AAC(3) family. It was initially found in clinical isolates of Enterobacter cloacae.

label.value: Target protecting FusB-type protein conferring resistance to Fusidic acid

value.value: Fusidic acid resistance determinants through the mediation of target protection. These protein drive the dissociation of EF-G from the ribosome thus counteracting the action of Fusidic acid.
msrF is an ABC-F binding cassette ribosomal protection protein. It confers resistance to macrolide antibiotics.
msrH is a ABC-F binding cassette ribosomal protection protein. It confers resistance to macrolide antibiotics.
mef(D) is a major facilitator superfamily efflux pump protein. It works together with the msr proteins to confer resistance to macrolide antibiotics.
RanB is the determinant of antibiotic resistance within the RanARanB ABC-type efflux system. It confers resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics.
RanA is a part of the RanARanB ABC-type efflux system. Alongside RanB, it confers resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics.
RanARanB is the combination of both RanA and RanB to form an ABC-type efflux system. RanB confers resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics.
OXA-899 is a class D beta-lactamase and part of the OXA family. It confers resistance to B-lactams and was originally found in Ralstonia pikettii.
OXA-898 is a class D beta-lactamase from the OXA family. It confers resistance to B-lactams and was originally found in Ralstonia pikettii.
GPC is a class A beta-lactamase family. It is found initially in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. It confers resistance to B-lactams.
GPC-1 is a class A beta-lactamase. It is part of the GPC beta-lactamase gene family. Originally found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Confers resistance to B-lactams.
A blaZ-like beta-lactamase found in S. Aureus.
A subunit of the qac multidrug efflux pump in Vibrio cholerae.
